adATLASVoiceIfNumber.name: adATLASVoiceIfNumber
adATLASVoiceIfNumber.description: The number of voice ports (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

adATLASVoiceIfTable.name: adATLASVoiceIfTable
adATLASVoiceIfTable.description: The ATLAS Voice Interface Status Table

adATLASVoiceIfEntry.name: adATLASVoiceIfEntry
adATLASVoiceIfEntry.description: An entry in the ATLAS Voice Interface Status Table

adATLASVoiceIfIndex.name: adATLASVoiceIfIndex
adATLASVoiceIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the object instance.

adATLASVoiceIfSlotNum.name: adATLASVoiceIfSlotNum
adATLASVoiceIfSlotNum.description: This variable indicates the slot number of a particular ATLAS module with a voice interface.

adATLASVoiceIfPortNum.name: adATLASVoiceIfPortNum
adATLASVoiceIfPortNum.description: This variable indicates the port number of a particular voice interface on an ATLAS module.

adATLASVoiceIfPortStat.name: adATLASVoiceIfPortStat
adATLASVoiceIfPortStat.description: This variable indicates the call or port status of a particular voice interface on an ATLAS module. Applicable voice interfaces for each option follow: 1 - 4 FXS, FXO, E&M 5 - 8 FXS, FXO 9 - 15 FXS 16 - 20 FXO 21 - 24 E&M

adATLASVoiceIfTxSignalBits.name: adATLASVoiceIfTxSignalBits
adATLASVoiceIfTxSignalBits.description: Transmit signaling bits: ABCD represented as a character string of 1's and 0's.

adATLASVoiceIfRxSignalBits.name: adATLASVoiceIfRxSignalBits
adATLASVoiceIfRxSignalBits.description: Receive signaling bits: ABCD represented as a character string of 1's and 0's.

adATLASVoiceTstTable.name: adATLASVoiceTstTable
adATLASVoiceTstTable.description: The ATLAS Voice Interface Test Table

adATLASVoiceTstEntry.name: adATLASVoiceTstEntry
adATLASVoiceTstEntry.description: An entry in the ATLAS Voice Interface Test Table

adATLASVoiceTstIndex.name: adATLASVoiceTstIndex
adATLASVoiceTstIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the object instance.

adATLASVoiceTst2W.name: adATLASVoiceTst2W
adATLASVoiceTst2W.description: This variable indicates the 2 Wire Test setting on a particular voice interface on an ATLAS module. Applicable voice interfaces for each option follow: 1 FXS, FXO, E&M 2 - 4 FXO 5 - 9 FXS 10 - 11 E&M

adATLASVoiceTstTxABCD.name: adATLASVoiceTstTxABCD
adATLASVoiceTstTxABCD.description: This variable indicates the Transmit Signaling Bits Test setting on a particular voice interface on an ATLAS module.

adATLASVoiceTst1kHzTone.name: adATLASVoiceTst1kHzTone
adATLASVoiceTst1kHzTone.description: This variable indicates the Tone Test setting on a particular voice interface on an ATLAS module. Near is for sending tone towards the 2W port. Far is for sending tone towards the PCM (DS0 or B-Channel).

adATLASVoiceTstLpBk.name: adATLASVoiceTstLpBk
adATLASVoiceTstLpBk.description: This variable indicates the Loopback Test setting on a particular voice interface on an ATLAS module.
